Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add
the @sweet potato{300%g}(diced) and half the @Mexican style spice mix{1}.
Season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally until
the sweet potato begins to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Add to the #pan{}
with the sweet potato. Cook until softened, ~{3%minutes}. Roughly chop the
@coriander{}(chopped, stalks and all). Chop the @tomatoes{2%medium} into
roughly 1cm chunks. Mix the coriander and tomato together in a #bowl{}.

Lower the heat on the sweet potato and add a splash of water to the pan. Cover
with a #lid{} or #foil{} and cook until soft enough to eat, another
~{7-8%minutes}.

> Shake the pan every 2 mins or so to make sure the sweet potato isn't catching.

If the pan is dry, add another splash of water, replace the lid and keep cooking.

Pop the @British turkey steaks{2} on a #plate{}, drizzle with oil and season
with @salt{}, @pepper{} and the remaining Mexican spice. Rub the flavours over
the meat.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Pop onto a #baking tray{} and grill until browned on the outside and cooked
through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> The turkey is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Add a squeeze of lime juice to the tomato and
coriander. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add a little more lime juice if
you want to!

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1/2%tin} in a #sieve{}. Add the black beans to
the sweet potato once it is cooked. Stir and cook until the beans are piping hot,
~{2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Share between your #bowls{}. Slice
the turkey and pop on top of your beans. Finish with the tomato salsa.